# plan.md Standards

- Build the plan from current MVP + PRD only; no speculative features.
- Structure sections in this order:
  1. Goal and scope
  2. Assumptions and constraints
  3. Milestones (timeboxed)
  4. Sprint backlog by priority
  5. Dependencies and risks
  6. Definition of done
  7. Metrics and validation checkpoints
- Convert requirements into actionable tasks with clear outputs.
- Prefer vertical slices (end-to-end usable pieces) over isolated technical tasks.
- Include explicit verification for each milestone (unit, integration, and UAT signals).

# Prioritization Policy

- Prioritize safety-critical and retention-driving capabilities first.
- Keep tasks small enough to complete in one focused session when possible.
- Flag blocked items with required decision/input owner.
